Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
ref: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.25, p.780 (1982)
title: Elastic Photon Scattering Between 9.5 and 12 Mev In Pb-208 and Pb-206.

x4freetext: ELASTIC PHOTON SCATTERING BETWEEN 9.5 AND 12 MEV
IN PB-208 AND PB-206.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.25, p.780 (1982)

x4codes.hlp: University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign, IL, United States of America
University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign, IL, United States of America

x4freetext: ILLINOIS MICROTRON USING A
SUPERCONDUCTING LINAC (MUSL-2).
THE DETECTOR WAS CYLINDRICAL AND WAS ABOUT
15 CM IN DIAMETER AND 23 CM DEEP.
TWO PB TARGETS WITH DIFFERENT ISOTOPIC ENRICHMENT
WERE USED TO SEPARATE THE SCATTERING DUE TO PB-208
AND PB-206. A PBC(O-3) POWDER TARGET THAT WAS PACKED
INTO A LUCITE BOX WAS ENRICHED IN PB-208; IT CONTAINED
TARGET ENRICHED IN PB-206 WAS A SOLID METAL WHICH
DIRECT MEASUREMENTS OF CROSS SECTION VALUES FOR
COINCIDENCE COUNTS BETWEEN THE TAGGED ELECTRONS FROM
MICROTRON AND THE SCATTERING GAMMA-QUANTA DETECTOR.
THE STATISTICAL ERRORS ARE PRESENTED ONLY. THE
SYSTEMATIC UNCERTAINTIES WERE ESTIMATED TO BE
PROBABLY LESS THAN 10%.  FOR THE SMALLEST MEASURED
CROSS SECTIONS (I.E., EQUAL TO OR LESS THAN 0.03
MB/SR) THERE ARE ADDITIONAL UNCERTAINTIES CAUSED BY
THE DIFFICULTY OF SEPARATING RELIABLY THE ELASTIC
SCATTERING PEAK FROM THE BACKGROUND IN THE GAMMA-RAY
SPECTRUM MEASURED WITH THE NAI PHOTON DETECTOR. THE
DATA POINTS BELOW 9.7 MEV FOR PB-208 AND BELOW 10 MEV
FOR ENRICHED PB-206 TARGET MIGHT, THEREFORE, HAVE
LARGER SYSTEMATIC ERRORS.
CORRECTIONS FOR GEOMETRIC FACTORS AND FOR THE ATOMIC
ABSORPTION OF PHOTONS IN THE TARGETS MAY HAVE
CONTRIBUTED AN UNCERTAINTY OF 5% OR LESS.
THE ELASTIC PHOTON SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS OF
PB-208 AND PB-206 WERE MEASURED AT 90 AND 135
DEGREES IN THE ENERGY RANGE FROM 9.5 TO 12 MEV WITH A
TAGGED PHOTON BEAM WHOSE ENERGY SPREAD WAS ABOUT 125
KEV. THE PB-206 CROSS SECTION RISES MONOTONICALLY
WITH ENERGY, AND IS CONSISTENT WITH A TOTAL PHOTON
INTERACTION CROSS SECTION WHICH HAS A LORENTZIAN
ENERGY DEPENDENCE WITH A PEAK CROSS SECTION OF 650 MB
AT 13.6 MEV AND A WIDTH ABOUT 3.8 MEV. THE PB-208
SCATTERING CROSS SECTION IS LARGER AND HAS SOME RAPID
VARIATIONS WITH ENERGY; THERE IS A NARROW EXTRA PEAK
NEAR 10.04 MEV AND THERE ARE ABRUPT INCREASES IN THE
CROSS SECTION JUST BELOW 10.6 AND 11.3 MEV. THE
RELATIVE SCATTERING OBSERVED AT THE TWO ANGLES
INDICATES THAT ALL OF THE SCATTERING, INCLUDING THE
RAPID VARIATIONS WITH ENERGY, IS DOMINATED DY DIPOLE
INTERACTIONS.

x4freetext: ONCE THE DOMINANCE OF E1 PROCESSES HAS
BEEN ESTABLISHED, THE MEASURED SCATTERING
DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION AT 90 DEGREES CAN BE
CONVERTED TO THE SCATTERING CROSS SECTION
INTEGRATED OVER ANGLE SIG(EG) WHICH FOR E1
SCATTERING IS GIVEN BY EQUATION:
SIG(EG) = 16.76 (D-SIG/D-OMEGA(E,90-DEGREES)).
